en_223431_0	An Army soldier and an Army civil servant have been arrested in Kurunegala for illegal possession of two T-56 rifles, a magazine with 10 live bullets and components of firearms and equipment.
en_223431_1	The Police Media Spokespersonâ€™s Office stated that the suspects were arrested at the Kurunegala-Goa Kotuwa junction.
en_223431_2	Police stopped a suspicious looking motorbike and during the search operation found a T-56 rifle and a magazine with live bullets hidden inside the jacket worn by the rider.
en_223431_3	The arrested rider is a 46-year-old Army soldier attached to the Buttala Army Camp a resident of Dahigamuwa, Kurunegala.
en_223431_4	The pillion arrested in this incident is a 37-year-old civil servant attached to the Wathupitiwala - Vijayaba Infantry Regiment residing in Hanwella.
en_223431_5	The police media unit further stated that the Police searched the homes of the suspects deploying an official police dog and found firearms and equipment including another T-56 rifle, a T-56 rifle cleaning kit, and an air rifle made in Italy.
